    <h1>Other high&#xAD;lights</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201006/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-06"><time>2020-10-06</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE ARTS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>DANC­ING AT DUSK</p>
    <p>In this dance film, leg­endary Ger­man chore­og­ra­pher Pina Bausch’s Rite Of Spring is per­formed on a beach in Toubab Dialaw, Sene­gal, at sun­set.</p>
    <p>Filmed as the world de­scended into lock­down, it doc­u­ments the last re­hearsal of 38 dancers spe­cially as­sem­bled from 14 African coun­tries.</p>
    <p>It is pro­duced by Bri­tish dance house Sadler’s Wells, Sene­galese school Ecole des Sables and the Pina Bausch Foun­da­tion in Ger­many.</p>
    <p>Where: Sis­tic Live</p>
    <p>When: Oct 12 to 31</p>
    <p>Ad­mis­sion: $12</p>
    <p>Info: Avail­able for Sin­ga­pore-based au­di­ences only</p>
    <p>OPEN CALL</p>
    <p>These seven short works by lo­cal artists, sub­mit­ted in re­sponse to the Es­planade’s open call dur­ing the Covid-19 out­break, ex­plore be­ing on pause and the pos­si­bil­i­ties in­her­ent in a state of sus­pen­sion.</p>
    <p>Ber­nice Lee and Adele Goh syn­chro­nise their bod­ies in the palin­dromic piece Uni­son, while Sand­hya Suresh and Dita Ja­cob jux­ta­pose the prac­tice of clas­si­cal In­dian dance form Odissi and the body of a con­tem­po­rary dancer in Body Lan­guage III.</p>
    <p>Where: Sis­tic Live</p>
    <p>When: Oct 18, 3pm live stream; avail­able on­line un­til Oct 31. Ad­di­tional live streams of</p>
    <p>You Are Fac­ing Your­self You Are Fac­ing Me by art nam­ing on the Es­planade’s YouTube chan­nel on Oct 18, 5 and 6pm Ad­mis­sion: Free</p>

